He's told the gathering that the fourth industrial revolution affects all developing nations and the task now is to stimulate investment. JOHANNESBURG - Russian President Vladimir Putin  has told the BRICS  forum in Sandton he hopes closer partnerships between the group's members in the digital economy will bring further development. He's told the gathering that the fourth industrial revolution affects all developing nations and the task now is to stimulate investment. Putin also says he supports the creation of regional centres for a BRICS Bank and would like to discuss the possibility of having an office in Russia. (Edited by Thapelo Lekabe)